observations.recommendation:
We recommended that the Municipal Mayor direct the Municipal Accountant and the Municipal Treasurer to:
a. reclassify the road lots from Land account (1-07-01-010) to Infrastructure Assets - Road Network (1-07-03-010) account in conformity with COA Circular No. 2015-008;
b. drop from the Lots and road lots owned by schools and the Provincial Government were properly dropped from the book;
c. adjust the recorded value of land and road lots based on acquisition cost and/or fair value as provided under PPSAS 17 for fair presentation of both accounts in the RPCPPE and the financial statements;
d. to record all land and road lots owned by the Municipality in the books of accounts and reconcile the respective records of the Accounting and Municipal Treasurer’s Office.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor direct the Municipal Accountant and the Municipal Treasurer to:
a. reclassify the road lots from Land account (1-07-01-010) to Infrastructure Assets - Road Network (1-07-03-010) account in conformity with COA Circular No. 2015-008;
b. drop from the RPCPPE the lots and road lots owned by the schools and the Provincial Government of Cavite, respectively, including the building under TDRP No. 14-0004-00227;
c. adjust the recorded value of land and road lots based on acquisition cost and/or fair value as provided under PPSAS 17 for fair presentation of both accounts in the RPCPPE and the financial statements;
d. to record all land and road lots owned by the Municipality in the books of accounts and reconcile the respective records of the Accounting and Municipal Treasurer’s Office.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor instruct the Municipal Accountant to:
1. Revert the Accounts Payable amounting to P8,744.48 which had been outstanding for more than two years and against which no actual claims has been filed nor were supported with valid documents to the unappropriated surplus;
2. Deposit to the Bureau of Treasury the amount of P2,400.00 representing the unexpended balance of trust liability in conformity with COA Circular Nos. Nos. 76-45 and 2015-009.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor direct:
the Municipal Accountant and the Municipal Treasurer to continue their efforts in reconciling their respective records to ascertain the reliability of the  balances of the PPE accounts  reflected in the financial statements.;
the Municipal  Accountant to verify the actual use of the land included by the Municipal Treasurer in the RPCPPE on  the basis of Tax Declarations under the name of the Municipality and record the same to Land or Public Infrastructure-Road Network  account, as appropriate;
the Inventory Committee to properly identify the buildings supported by Tax Declarations under the name of the Municipality to facilitate reconciliation of the RPCPPE and accounting records; and
the Municipal Treasurer to maintain Property Cards for individual property item owned by the Municipality for control purposes and keep track of the record of the property from acquisition, custody, repair,  to its disposal.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor direct the Municipal Engineer/BAC Chairman to ensure that:
a list of the  Municipality’s  programs/projects and activities, inclusive of those for implementation and non-infrastructure projects is submitted to the Audit Team at the beginning of the year;
relevant information regarding the PPAs of the Municipality be posted in  signboards or black/bulletin boards  following the provisions of the cited Circular;
the Audit Team  be informed that the appropriate project signboards and/or notices have been  posted  within ten (10) days after the award of the infrastructure project or before the start of the program/activity; and
maintain updated Project Status based on the data sourced from the monthly monitoring report prepared by Municipality.
